Simple Exploration

DF=read_csv(('../../Data/1999_2021/aggragate_daily_data_2000to2020.csv'))
## Warning: Missing column names filled in: 'X1' [1]
## 
## -- Column specification --------------------------------------------------------
## cols(
##   X1 = col_double(),
##   date = col_date(format = ""),
##   energy_charge = col_double(),
##   effluent_flow = col_double(),
##   influent_flow = col_double(),
##   volume_used = col_double(),
##   poured_flow = col_double(),
##   water_level = col_double(),
##   energy_generated = col_double(),
##   energy_stored = col_double(),
##   maximum_demand = col_double()
## )
DF=DF %>% mutate(year=year(date), month=month(date),day=day(date)) %>% mutate(day_year=yday(date))
DF %>% mutate(month_day=100*month+day) %>% ggplot(aes(x=day_year, y=water_level,color=factor(year)))+geom_line()

DF=DF%>%  group_by(year,month) %>% summarise(water_level=mean(water_level)) 
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
DF %>% ggplot(aes(x=month,color=factor(year),y=water_level))+geom_line()

dim(DF)
## [1] 240   3

Auto Arima

DF=DF %>% filter(year>=2008) %>%  mutate(year_month=year*100+month) %>%  arrange(year_month)
y=ts(DF$water_level,start=2008,frequency = 12)
a1 <- subset(y, end = 120)
a2 <- subset(y, start = 121)
y=a1
ggtsdisplay(y)

ggtsdisplay(diff(y))

Model=Arima(y,c(0,1,0),c(1,1,0))
checkresiduals(Model)

## 
##  Ljung-Box test
## 
## data:  Residuals from ARIMA(0,1,0)(1,1,0)[12]
## Q* = 32.822, df = 23, p-value = 0.08422
## 
## Model df: 1.   Total lags used: 24
Model
## Series: y 
## ARIMA(0,1,0)(1,1,0)[12] 
## 
## Coefficients:
##          sar1
##       -0.5606
## s.e.   0.0809
## 
## sigma^2 estimated as 0.4054:  log likelihood=-101.89
## AIC=207.77   AICc=207.89   BIC=213.12
y_pred=forecast(Model,12)
autoplot(y_pred)+autolayer(a2)

#Mean Squared Error
sum((y_pred$mean-a2)^2)

rain_df=read_csv('../../Data/historic_weather.csv')
## 
## -- Column specification --------------------------------------------------------
## cols(
##   date = col_date(format = ""),
##   hour = col_double(),
##   station = col_character(),
##   rain_mm = col_double(),
##   temp_max = col_double(),
##   temp_min = col_double()
## )
rain_df=rain_df %>% mutate(day=day(date), month=month(date), year_day=yday(date),year=year(date))
rain_df %>% group_by(year,month,day,year_day,date) %>% 
  summarize(rain_mm=sum(rain_mm)) %>% filter(rain_mm>0) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=year_day,y=rain_mm,color=factor(year)))+geom_point()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year', 'month', 'day', 'year_day'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

rain_df %>% group_by(year,month) %>% 
  summarize(rain_mm=sum(rain_mm)) %>% filter(rain_mm>0) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=month,y=rain_mm,color=factor(year)))+geom_point()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

Rainy days per year

rain_df %>% group_by(year, month, day, date) %>% summarise(rain_mm=sum(rain_mm,na.rm=TRUE)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% mutate(is_rainy=(rain_mm>0)) %>% group_by(year,month) %>% summarize(rainy_days=sum(is_rainy)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=month,y=rainy_days,color=factor(year)))+geom_line( )
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year', 'month', 'day'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

rain_df %>% group_by(year, month, day, date) %>% summarise(rain_mm=sum(rain_mm,na.rm=TRUE)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% mutate(is_rainy=(rain_mm>0)) %>% group_by(year,month) %>% summarize(rainy_days=sum(is_rainy)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=month,y=rainy_days,fill=factor(year)))+geom_bar(stat='identity')
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year', 'month', 'day'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

rain_df %>% group_by(year, month, day, date) %>% summarise(rain_mm=sum(rain_mm,na.rm=TRUE)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% mutate(is_rainy=(rain_mm>0)) %>% group_by(year) %>% summarize(rainy_days=sum(is_rainy)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=year,y=rainy_days))+geom_bar(stat = 'identity')+geom_text(aes(label=rainy_days))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year', 'month', 'day'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

rain_var=rain_df %>% group_by(year, month, day, date) %>% summarise(rain_mm=sum(rain_mm,na.rm=TRUE)) %>% 
    ungroup() %>%  arrange(date)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year', 'month', 'day'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
rain_var <- rain_var$rain_mm

rain_df=read_csv('../../Data/historic_weather.csv')
## 
## -- Column specification --------------------------------------------------------
## cols(
##   date = col_date(format = ""),
##   hour = col_double(),
##   station = col_character(),
##   rain_mm = col_double(),
##   temp_max = col_double(),
##   temp_min = col_double()
## )
rain_df=rain_df %>% mutate(day=day(date), month=month(date), year_day=yday(date),year=year(date)) %>% 
  group_by(year,month,station) %>% 
  summarize(rain_mm=sum(rain_mm)) %>% ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year', 'month'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
rain_df=rain_df %>% spread(station,rain_mm)

x1=rain_df %>% filter(year<=2018) %>% as.matrix()
x2=rain_df %>% filter(year>=2019,year<=2019) %>% as.matrix()

x1[is.na(x1)] <- 0
x2[is.na(x2)] <- 0
DF=read_csv(('../../Data/1999_2021/aggragate_daily_data_2000to2020.csv'))
## Warning: Missing column names filled in: 'X1' [1]
## 
## -- Column specification --------------------------------------------------------
## cols(
##   X1 = col_double(),
##   date = col_date(format = ""),
##   energy_charge = col_double(),

##   maximum_demand = col_double()
## )
DF=DF %>% mutate(year=year(date), month=month(date),day=day(date)) %>% mutate(day_year=yday(date)) %>% arrange(date)
DF %>% mutate(month_day=100*month+day) %>% ggplot(aes(x=day_year, y=water_level,color=factor(year)))+geom_line()

DF=DF%>%  group_by(year,month) %>% summarise(water_level=mean(water_level)) %>% ungroup() %>% arrange(year,month) %>% filter(year>=2007)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
y=ts(DF$water_level,start=2007,frequency = 12)
a1 <- subset(y, end = 144)
a2 <- subset(y, start = 145)
y=a1
ggtsdisplay(y)

ggtsdisplay(diff(y))

checkresiduals(Model)
